graph/adjacencymatrix.detaildescription:
The action converts graphs into a matrix based on a cost-map, the first argument can be a string with dense or sparse for defining the returned matrix, after that a cost-map cann be set or a fixed numerical value for defining the cost of an edge, all other arguments are graphs, for each graph the matrix and vertex list is returned, the action never fails <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>[M1|V1|M2|V2]=graph/adjacencymatrix("dense|sparse",CostMap,Graph1,Graph2);
[M3|V3|M4|V4]=graph/adjacencymatrix(CostMap,Graph1,Graph2);
[M1|V1|M2|V2]=graph/adjacencymatrix("dense|sparse",1,Graph1,Graph2);
[M3|V3|M4|V4]=graph/adjacencymatrix(1,Graph1,Graph2);
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

collection/multimap/asmap.detaildescription:
Actions translates multimap objects into map objects, action never fails <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>X=collection/multimap/asmap(MultiMap);
[A|B]=collection/multimap/asmap(MultiMap1,MultiMap2);
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

math/blas/matrix/assign.detaildescription:
The action assign the first argument to all other arguments which must be a matrix <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>math/blas/matrix/assign(2,Matrix1,[Matrix2,Matrix3]);
math/blas/matrix/assign(AssignMatrix,Matrix1,[Matrix2,Matrix3]);
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

math/blas/vector/assign.detaildescription:
The action assign the first argument to all other arguments which must be vectors <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>math/blas/vector/assign(2,Vector1,[Vector2,Vector3]);
math/blas/vector/assign(AssignVector,Vector1,[Vector2,Vector3]);
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

collection/multimap/create.detaildescription:
The action creates a multi-hashmap object and returns the object, optional arguments must be even and it will create a key-value structure, the action fails on an odd number of arguments except zero only <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>M1=collection/multimap/create();
M2=collection/multimap/create("key1",123,["Key2","Value2"]);
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

collection/list/create.detaildescription:
Creates a list of the arguments, so each argument of the action is put to the list, is the argument empty an empty-list object will be returned, the action fails never <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>L1=collection/list/create("a",1,["b",2]);
L2=collection/list/create();
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

collection/map/get.detaildescription:
Returns values of the map which is referenced by the key, the action fails never, the first argument is the map object, all other arguments are the keys <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>V1=collection/map/get(Map,"key");
[V2|V3]=collection/map/get(Map,"Key1","Key2");
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->

graph/spanningtree.detaildescription:
The action creates from each graph argument a spanning tree, if the first argument is a cost-map for edges the numerical values are used for the spanning tree <!-- htmlmin:ignore --><pre><code>[SP1|SP2]=graph/spanningtree(Graph1,Graph2);
[SP3|SP4]=graph/spanningtree(CostMap,Graph3,Graph4);
</code></pre><!-- htmlmin:ignore -->
